<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I am the one who released the &quot;rideable beasts&quot; info</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Jon">Jon</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:23 a.m. 21/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I am the one who released the &quot;rideable beasts&quot; info<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/e_ci.cgi?read=80" TARGET=_self>Re: Rideable Beast</A> (Faliuden)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Firstly i would like to say to all you SCEPTICS out there who decided i was crazy when i told everybody about the rideable beasts - it's in your face now! I have just received an official statement from EQ (I used to work for Verant for the first 3 beta phases) that....

<P>&gt;>>>"Sometime next month we will be officially releasing the first of the rideable beasts: this selection will include
<BR>The Horse
<BR>The Brown Bear
<BR>and the Great Bat-
<BR>The horse is availiable to most all character classes and races (some exceptions include Ogres, Trolls, and Gnomes) the Brown bear will be availiable to Shaman's only (note this doesn't include the races listed above) and the Great Bat will be availiable strickly to Dark Elves. We are also currently working on formatting others though these will be all for now. Further details and rules will be released at a later date. We hope to have them up and running soon, and we hope that they enrich game enjoyability for all."<<<<<
<P>Well i'd like to see what you all have to say now!
<BR>I have to say i am extremely excited about this and i hope you are too! It may make my 6 hours of play a day i little easier- It'll mean my 18th level erudite wizard may be able to run away a little faster when he accidently picks on something too big! Well i hope to see you all soon and i hope you are as excited about this as i am! Goodbye for now!
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
